===Etymology 2===
{{zh-forms|alt=塍,堘}}
The Min native word for “paddy field; field”.

Etymology unknown. Chinese scholars identify {{och-l|塍|raised path between fields}} as the etymological character ({{zh-l|本字|tr=-}}), although {{w|Jerry Norman (sinologist)|Norman}} proposes that this is related to {{och-l|層|layer}}, reflecting the terraced fields commonly found in Fujian ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Compare also {{och-l|㽪|wet field}}.

